6. Discussion: The Bottleneck Creation Mechanism

6.1 The False Efficiency Curve

Short-term:
	•	Automation increases output
	•	Labor costs decrease

Mid-term:
	•	Skill pipeline collapses
	•	Error rates increase at higher tiers

Long-term:
	•	Production bottlenecks migrate upward
	•	Expert labor becomes scarce and expensive
	•	Systems slow despite “automation”

6.2 Critical Insight

Removing easy work does not remove difficulty—it concentrates it.

